name: Matt Clark
bio: Boutique Furniture | Design | Art | Spec Pieces

social_posts.post_text: Hey guy I’d love your feedback on my latest video!  You know where to find it, happy Tuesday!
Fresh dimensional sign for @ember_valley is all completed and ready for the new space, loving how the @rubiomonocoatusa natural gives the mahogany a subtle clean look, happy Thursday!

Merry Christmas everyone!  Tried out a new way to cook a prime rib, it came out absolutely delicious!  I always usually pull @ 123-125 but the carryover usually is just a little too much for my liking, this year I did at 118° with an 8.35lb roast and it was perfect.  Compound butter was rosemary, thyme, garlic, S&P, whipped taters were Yukon gold with heavy cream, butter, sour cream, sharp cheddar, S&P and chives, and of course a few cans of buttery corn.  Cheers!

What a fun year 2022 was, reflecting back on some exciting projects, I had some wonderful opportunities to make really exciting pieces.  I made my first slab-sectional/couch, delivered and finished the root table into @reddingraw, made a first conference/poker table combo, @joerogan received his resin art piece with the original @killcliff can, made my first 14’ single slab conference table with @superclearepoxy resin, really tried to dabble into the art market with a couple works, with that I will absolutely be working on more in 2023, and I also did my annual philanthropy work by selling an art piece and donating the $ to 2 families in need.  My main focus for this next year is hitting A goal of 200k subs on YT, explore into unknown realms of wood/mixed material work that make me uncomfortable, take risks, teach and share knowledge to the younger generation, and do more philanthropic work.  If you’ve read this far, thank you, I truly appreciate all of the support I’ve gotten this last year, but I have some slightly unfortunate news.. There has been some change in plans for my client with the big root and the fan root we purchased from @gl_veneer, we will not be using them for any future projects so they are for sale, or available on a commission through me for pieces of furniture/art.  Shoot me a message if you have any interest!  I hope you all have a wonderful 2023, get out there and build something, cheers!

Really loved making this art piece.  I have one more very similar claro walnut sunburst in STOCK that’s begging to be made into a luxury table tennis design/collectable art piece, I’d like to create something ultra unique!  Let’s work together, who’s ready?

Claro walnut slabs are a prized possession, one of the holy grails in our world of wood.  It’s plush, beautiful, juicy, and basically I feel I can eat it like a chocolate bar.  This 14’ table was such a challenge being solo, but the payoff was so worth it!  I’m ready for a 20’ challenge, let’s gooooo!  What’s your favorite slab species?

This commercial space that I made this 20’ conference coffee table for, definitely takes the cake in being one of the most amazing places I’ve been able to put my work. It is an old Ford manufacturing plant, it has amazing history and the original parts press is still in there, you can see in the back. Incredible!
Progress on the new art project for @rhillscasino, love the way it’s coming out, whatcha think?
Krispy 👌 All components cut out. Pumped to get some color and finish on.
Making progress with some color and paint, very excited to see this project through.

The components are all stained/painted and rough assembled.  Working on the detail side pieces now that will be matte black with some @rubiomonocoatusa pre color and charcoal 2C.  The white is latex paint, so it’s compatible with my CV finish that I’ll be spraying over the top of it all after I glue and pin nail all of the pieces in the correct location.  Excited to use @bidwellwoodandiron new steel French cleat system to hang this puppy too!

The 4 detail pieces came out really nice, love the way the @rubiomonocoatusa pre color black paired with 2C charcoal comes together. Such an amazing subtle matte black. I’m going to do one more coat of charcoal to bump the sheen, but otherwise we are ready for the finish process for the whole sign.

Everything is glued and attached, touched up and ready for finish. The dimensional detail pieces are coated with @rubiomonocoatusa and will get a final coating from @blacktailstudio new product N3 Nanofinish. Pumped to see this thing wrapped up!
The @rhillscasino main logo is wrapped!  What do you think?
The EV sign is all hung in it’s new space down in LA, the mahogany looks killer against the concrete wall!
If anyone wants to own this epic 800 acre ranch with my furniture featured in this log cabin guest house, let me know, it’s for sale!

It’s been two years since I completed and delivered this table for my aunt and uncle harry, it has to be one of my most memorable and special pieces to date, given the back story!  If you haven’t read about it before I will copy and paste it below, love this one!

**6 years ago when I started woodworking I visited a hardwood store in Chico Ca, and absolutely fell in love with with these two burned sycamore tree trunks, they had to be salvaged because a homeless group of people were burning the tree from the inside out to stay warm.  I couldn’t afford one at the time but I definitely saved some pictures for future potential projects.  3 years later I had a client interested in one, so I called back the hardwood store and my heart absolutely sank when they said the entire shop/inventory had recently burned down.. All gone (including the sycamore trunks)! Such a tragedy, pouted for a couple days but things went on.. Fast forward to last December when I picked up the redwood root from @gl_veneer, I spotted this piece that looked all too familiar at the top of a pile all covered up.  I asked Daniel, DUDE is that from Chico?! He said YES, my pops bought it right before their shop burned down.. I was just in awe and came to the conclusion that it was fate, told him to load her up too! - My aunt’s home burned in the Carr fire a couple years ago, and after she saw this, she immediately changed her mind from a barn wood table to this amazing piece, the burned insides kind of pay a small homage to the experience she went through. All in all it came full circle, and I’m super happy it is in the hands of someone who truly appreciates a one-of-a-kind furniture piece like this.  Seats 10 comfortably too!
APRIL FOOLS one day SALE!  Buy a custom solid bronze chess set with the table and chairs, and get a claro walnut sunburst ping pong table for FREE! 😲
🏔️ ranges
Which legs do you like? Steel plates sandwiching wood, or solid wood standalone?
WIP on this new sign, got the first coat of @rubiomonocoatusa on the oak today, now to finish sand and clear the claro, looking sharp!

Had the pleasure of seeing my last poker table works again today, helped my client move it to his pool house so he can actually start using it ;). Sunburst top from @gl_veneer still looking amazing with @superclearepoxy table top too!  Really loved making this piece, and definitely due for another since it’s already been a year since I made this one. Who’s next?
Made Greg a cedar parsons table for underneath his pavilion, came out sweet!  I’ve made this in dining table form before but never a coffee table, I’m digging it. Thoughts?

One of the coolest experiences I’ve had with GL is acquiring these two larger root systems, plans have changed with the current owners of them and they are both up FOR SALE as raw pieces, or commissioned work through me, the larger root is already milled and ready for a glass top, and the fan root has been sandblasted and ready for use for various functional art pieces.  Reach out via email or DM if serious inquiries.

I got the wall art installation about 90% done, thanks to my homie Greg for all the help!  I’ll be back tomorrow to fine tune everything and install all of the triangles that are surrounding the left and right side strips, 56 of them to be exact.  I’ll be sure to post some before and afters when it’s all buttoned up!  The new steel French cleat from @bidwellwoodandiron worked amazing, super strong and easy to install!
Probably the most stressful part of this project was hanging this large sign, but super happy with the final outcome!  Shoot me your thoughts on the whole piece, how do you think it came together?

One of my favorite parts of this project is all of the red oak material I used was from wood from the camp fire milled up from @bidwellwoodcompany, including the main logo, all of the red triangles and the strips that house them.  Such a fun project!

Sometimes you gotta make some changes, here’s some progress on the revised teeth art that’s going to be displayed and for sale at 
@jungleregroup ‘s new art show room featuring various local artists.  Lots more polishing to do, then I’ll be able to see what it looks like on their wall for the first time!

Revision complete on the teeth art, I used @superclearepoxy new art resin with some blue/green pigment and applied @blacktailstudio new N3 Nano to the entire piece, came out slick!  Will be on display and for sale at @jungleregroup in their art studio, what do you think of it now?

Finished up the install today at @jungleregroup super happy with the turn out.  The @blacktailstudio N3 makes this thing pop, and the @superclearepoxy new art resin is legit!  This is my first ever art works on display, very excited for people to see it in person, it’s available for purchase so go check it out ;)

Had to change up the extension system to something more beefy, ended up using @bidwellwoodandiron c-channel as the supports. It will stay hidden when not in use and will support a ton of weight, also features being adjustable in length of bracket exposure.  The extensions will be 55”x20”x2.5” thick solid monkey pod, excited to show this one!

Milled down and installed the 20” extension for the monkey pod table, I used 2 c-channels as my supports, there’s a very small amount of deflection when the weight is applied, I’d say this test is 190-200lbs, never know what kind of extracurricular activities that will be had, better safe than sorry :). I’d say this is a great way to do larger/thicker extensions with excessive weight, I get my steel channel and Rampa hardware from @bidwellwoodandiron, can’t wait to get finish on this one!
Love me some clean cuts ✂️
The extension system and panels are completed and installed, we’ve got a 9’ standalone table with extendability to just under 12 1/2’

All of the leg components are complete, did some mock up today on how the base will look with the top. I’m really loving the look, something about a 7° angle, whatcha think?  The middle sections are white oak that will be blackened with @rubiomonocoatusa, can’t wait!

Need your help!  I’m designing a new poker table and I need some feedback on the ones I’ve done prior and what I can change for a casino type playing experience but also more exclusive and extravagant.  The client wants 5-10 of them, but really is keen on leg room and playability. This design I did a few years ago I feel has the most leg room, but I like to change up designs for each new project, shoot me your thoughts on what you’d change with either the base or the top for true poker players, comfortability, luxury feel, and playability. Would be much appreciated!
Bases complete ✔️
Bottom is complete, legs are installed, now onto finishing out the top and the extensions then it’s a wrap!  Whatcha think?

The monkey pod extension table is complete, just a couple more coats of @blacktailstudio @n3nano and it’s a wrap!  This is ONE coat of his hard coat on top of a satin conversion varnish.  Can’t wait to see how much it pops when they’re all applied.  Definitely a new favorite of my table builds!
Completion on a project never felt so good, love the way this one turned out!  2 coats of @n3nano from @blacktailstudio, monkey pod from @gl_veneer, and the matte black is @rubiomonocoatusa.
Officially my largest cutting board to date @ 8.5’ x 8.5’. Yes you read that right, it’s an actual cutting board. Used @bidwellwoodcompany food grade finish, turned out great!
The start of another art project, this works will be mixed media - about a dozen various wood species, resin and billet bronze & brass.  Can you guess what it’s going to be?
Cutting board and table are landed and all set up, super excited to get these inside their new home safely.

So happy with this project, the delivery and install went very smooth.  The dining table is 9’ long and 55” wide for scale, and has extensions that lengthen it to just under 13’. The wood specie is monkey pod from @gl_veneer, and is finished in a sprayed conversion varnish topped with @n3nano finish for extra protection.  The matte black is from @rubiomonocoatusa, their pre color black paired with 2 coats of charcoal.  The island cutting board is solid walnut almost 2” thick, and measured just under 9’x9’, it’s finish with @atomicfinishes oil, I’m actually super excited about them using this as an actual cutting board, their vision is to in 15-20 years to obtain burn marks, scars and the patina an old school chopping block would have in a butcher shop.  New dining table table up next!

Top is completed! Black @superclearepoxy resin paired with a beautiful hard maple slab from @truwood_builders.  I’ll give this a couple days of cure time then top this puppy off with @n3nano.  Fabrication on deck
About 30% complete with the piece, have some fun plans for this one!  Do we know what it is yet?
Carved the frosting drips and added final coat of pigment resin, about 40% done now. So much more I have planned for this piece, color looks wild!

Such a fun day yesterday doing this test with @mbrinkleystudios, this is our second go around with topography carvings, this one being in white oak with the terrain up close to Shasta Dam.  This is potentially going to be two large scale art pieces being separated by the middle tv/fireplace wall.  Using @amanatool spectra bits from @toolstoday on this one, the finish came out spectacular and this is just their 1/8” ball nose bit, can’t wait for the 1/16” detail!
Name the sprinkles’ wood species!  Rough shaped them today, and added some bling, really excited for this one! #whenyouseeit
Bling sprinkle
First vertical look of the donut, we’re about 80% complete.  Just have to fine tune the sprinkles then it will be complete!What do you think of the progress?
Splash of 🫐 white oak - Home-r stretch!  #homersimpsondonut

Dry fitted the sprinkles, just about done! This will be for sale upon completion, will be hung with a french cleat in any orientation desired!  @n3nano is the final step to wrap her up!  Which donut shop should snag this?  Comment below and tag which one you think should rock this puppy :)
7 species of wood with a splash of solid bronze, can you name them all?
Have some Christmas charcuterie gifts up for grabs!  Sequoia Redwood Burl, olive, cottonwood, willow and black walnut butcher block cutting boards.  Shoot me a message to snag em’
Little sus Matt, little bit sus.. Been working on some massive 10’ long big timber white oak console tables, definitely getting my workout in 💪🏻
